    <stitle>GENERAL INSTRUMENT ELECTRONIC PROGRAMMABLE SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER - ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Turn key switch to OFF position before adjusting or installing sensor.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
            <title>SENSOR ADJUSTMENT</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08033_8.xml" xrefid="f0803306">Figure 6</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="f0803306"/>
                or
                <xref refid="f0803307"/>
                <hotlnk document="s08033_8.xml" xrefid="f0803307">Figure 7</hotlnk>
                for this procedure.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Identify sensor connectors if more than (1). Disconnect sensor from vehicle harness.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen sensor lock nut and back nut off far enough to allow sensor adjustment.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn sensor in until the sensor bottoms out against the engine flywheel (tachometer
                    sensor) or transmission gear (speedometer sensor). Back out (1) full turn.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten sensor lock nut using wrench to prevent sensor from turning while tightening
                    lock nut. Tighten lock nut to specifications (refer to
                    <xref refid="x0803305"/>
                    <hotlnk document="s08033_24.xml" xrefid="x0803305">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect sensor lead to vehicle harness connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Run engine to test tachometer or road/dynamometer test to check speedometer.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
